article.headline: Butler has off night for Aggies
article.linkText: Utah State wins close one from UC Irvine
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Mark Brown scored 17 points and Spencer Nelson added 14, leading No. 24 Utah State to a 59-56 victory over UC Irvine on Saturday night. The Aggies' 21st victory in 22 games enabled Utah State (24-2, 16-1 Big West Conference) to maintain its half-game conference lead over second-place Pacific. Ross Schraeder scored 20 points for the Anteaters (11-15, 6-10), who have lost nine of 11. Stanislav Zuzak added 12 points. UC Irvine held a 38-37 lead when Utah State used an 11-2 run to move ahead 48-40 with 7:41 to play. The Anteaters closed to 55-53 with 1:47 remaining, but Brown made an 8-foot driving jumper and two free throws to extend the Aggies' lead to 59-53 with 48.4 seconds left. UC Irvine had a chance to force overtime after Schraeder made a 3-point shot with 38.4 seconds to play and Brown missed two free throws with 15.6 seconds left. But Schraeder missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer. Utah State made eight of 13 field-goal attempts and 15 of 20 free throws in the second half in tying the school record for most conference victories in a season.
